We called the following day to let them know what happened and they said okay let‚Äôs schedule an appointment for that day. Turned out they called me back about 30 min later saying their technician is sick and out for the day. Like come on don‚Äôt you guys work at the same place? Is there no communication? < review>
I've never seen or heard of this shop before. I needed an alignment done on my car asap from just getting it back from a shop that installed some coilovers for me. I wanted to find a shop that would be able to perform an alignment on a lowered car. For one there were no other shops available to do so and couldn't take me without an appointment. I called johns shop and was welcomed there soon as I could get there. This shop is it man. Not only do they have a perfect alignment machine for lowered cars but the technicians there know what they are talking about and the shop is clean and makes you feel comfortable walking in. They found one of my control arms were busted. Told me they could have the parts there that day and have them installed for me with an alignment for a great price. I couldn't leave my car there. They hooked me up the best they could with an alignment to get by for the day and had me come in then next day. Boom showed up, dropped my car off, called me back when John said it would be done and I couldn't be any happier. Thank you John and the rest of the team there not only for being very professional but making me feel like I was part of the family and for also doing a fantastic job. I have any more problems this is my shop to go to.</review>

Dr Fram is very competent and personable. I was there a long time for prep etc but  my procedure was quick;  I felt like I was treated well and had good professional care.  Where they could improve their service would be to give better instructions with regard to home care. I was told I would have floaters; I did not know how long they would last, how long to expect the dilation to last, and what restrictions I was expected to follow . At the time I didn't think to ask; it was after I returned home when the office was already closed that I realized I needed more direction. It's always a good idea to write down questions before arriving at any office, due to the fact that when going into any kind of procedure the brain is only focused on the immediate inconvenience; hence, clarity is limited. Because of Covid, my husband couldn't be in the waiting room. He was downstairs with no seating for over 2 hours and couldn't stay outside because at 6pm it was very cold. <gmapID>0x80c28705bfabe36f:0x67cb0463a1356dc4</gmapID>< user>
109653600686349308993< /user>
<Review>IN SHORT:
I am VERY disappointed with ACE Automotive. Don't go there, especially for an estimate. They will charge you for doing nothing! I wanted to give them 2 stars because I think they had a good manner about them and were polite, if dismissive of what I thought might be wrong, but charging a customer for doing nothing is VERY POOR CUSTOMER SERVICE. It seems that the only month it might be safe to go there is July, when AAA comes by to give them a certificate assuring they have great customer service.

FULL STORY:
I was referred to Ace by Kiwi Motors down the street who did excellent work on my wife's Honda. Went in to Ace because my car was running a little rough and there was an oil leak and some door handles that needed to be replaced. I liked the guys when I first went in, they assured me that they would give the car a thorough look over and let me know what needed to be done. I had the car in by 8:00AM today to give them the maximum time to look it over. I let them know that I didn't have much money, only a few hundred to do repairs for an oil leak and maybe a few other things if they were affordable. I brought the new door handles I ordered online in with me. By 10:30, they called me back. I won't name names, but the person on the other end of the phone assured me that he had looked it over for half an hour: The rough idle was from old engine mounts. Replacing the door handles using the parts I had brought to them would cost me $175. He couldn't check on the oil leak because he would have to take the covers off to find out where it was and that would cost a lot in labor, but the operation was likely to involve a repair that would cost over $500. That was only to fix the one possible oil leak and timing belt, because it was bound to break and strand me if I didn't take care of it (My wife had a new timing belt put on her car at Kiwi for about $250). There would be an additional $150+ charge to do a valve-cover gasket replacement (A simple DIY operation, less than $50 for parts, oil and oil pan at any automotive supplier and about 30-45 minutes to do yourself). Then he told me that there was a problem with the BRAND NEW alternator that I had installed less than six months ago. He suggested that I needed an entirely new alternator, which would be over $175 for them to do with labor and parts, because there was a spark gap in the lug holding the lead into the alternator and he didn't want to touch it because it was hot. I immediately went to get my car, this sounded fishy...

I was charged $45 to get my key back for nothing besides some advice (I don't know what is laborious about driving my car into the port and looking under the hood for 20 minutes, probably less). I drove it home, replaced the washer and lug-nut holding the lead on the alternator. The lead was clean; there was no melted metal and no corrosion or whitening/blackening from sparking. Took me LESS than one minute to do everything. No more alternator light. Nothing wrong with alternator. Took the door panels off and replaced the door handles, replaced door panels. Less than 30 minutes to do both handles myself!

I called another local place (Big John's, THANK YOU) and asked them what they would charge for an estimate and a thorough look over of the car: Nothing. Estimates and inspections done for free. The guy even gave me advice on how to do some of the work myself. THAT is great customer service.<//Review><user_name>Paul Newland< /user_name><time>1381436776497</time><Rating>1</Rating><Response>None<//Response><Pictures>None<//Pictures></record>

< review>
Not the greatest experience at all. I went here thinking that all I needed to do was rent my truck, per usual, and be gone. First, the rude woman at the front desk told me that I could not use a debit card at her location at all.

Upon questioning her further, she been clarified that I could not use a debit card if I was renting out a van, but if I wanted to use the truck, I could use my debit card for that.

Any customer service rep that works for U-Haul could look at my account and easily tell this woman that I have never paid a $100 security deposit for renting a U-Haul Van. However, that's what she insisted that I needed to do, I needed to pay $100 security deposit.

She then try to Hard Sell the insurance for the U-Haul, claiming that I would need it for the rain, because the drivers on the road get crazy when it rains. Once I told her that I couldn't do $100, she didn't even care if I left out of the store or not.

I immediately called another location, and they charged my debit card $47 for the entire fee, before I even made it to their location. They clearly need better customer service agent at this location.

However, if it's not broke, they don't need to fix it. I would NOT highly recommend this place to anyone that I know. There are enough attitude in Los Angeles, why do I need to come here or send my friends here to experience that?</review>

professional handled to our satisfaction by Craig and his techs.   I have
found Craig to always be available to answer my questions regardless of the subject matter.   We would buy another trailer from this facility based largely on the service we have received from staff, especially Craig.</Text>

< text>
We drove to Atascadero from Beaumont to View a 2018 40ft Big Horn 5th wheel in February 2018. We sent the full payment a few days later and drove back after the PDI. When we showed up to pick up the unit, the right side panel was damaged. We were reluctant to take the unit with this damage. David the sales manager assured us that the panel would be ordered and replaced. I called a week later and talked to the Service manager. He told me the panel was on order. I called every week and was told the same thing. Then after waiting till June I called again only to find out that the service manager no longer works there and the panel was not ordered. I have now called twice more. $68,000 on a new unit that was damaged by employees at this Dealer and they do not want to take responsibility.<//text>

I'm changing my review after our purchase was complete.  To start out every single employee was nothing but friendly and helpful!  The owner was onsite and just seemed like someone you would want to be friends with.  We did our financing through them and it was fast and easy.  We even had our 1 year old and 3 year old sit with us while we went through the process.  Fast forward...  Once we purchased our trailer we were treated like second class citizens.  Customer service was terrible and they ended up selling us a trailer that was to big for our truck.</text>

<user>105906398293879803570<//user>< review>
I was asked by Pacific Coast RV's lawyer on May 17th, 2016 to "cease and desist" regarding my past review and experience with their company and it's employees.  I was asked to remove the post not because it was non-factual, but because I called them a name that to me represented the way I was treated by their company. I was born and raised in San Luis Obispo County, where I was taught the meaning of your "word" and a hand shake, because that is something that people judge you by.  It's too bad that others don't realize how important that is in a "large" but still very small community as ours. (The one star rating is given only because without it I couldn't post my review.)<//review>

<GmapID>0x80dd2b9633d91d71:0xdd3a30bcf1aa73b9< /GmapID><user_name>Jodi Linwood</user_name>< review>
Portion size. YUP. Unlimited Ban Chan. YUP. Great for my sick friend. YUP.

We wanted army stew, and looked for places around us. This happens to be one of the many few places(in the area) that actually have this stew, in comparison to all the existing kbbq places.

We got the hot pot - Base Army Stew(w/ serving size for two) and we were absolutely demolished. If you consider the ban chan and the red bean rice they give you, that's an insane amount of food that I think could have filled up to 3, maybe even 4 people.

They did not skip out on the sausage at all, and they have fish cake for sides. Tons and tons of protein!

This is a hole in the wall gem that blessed my sick friend's sinuses, maybe it'll gain more popularity as army stew becomes as popular as Korean barbecue.<//review>

<rate>4< /rate><Review>This place is a small local Korean restaurant that serves very basic, but hearty food. These types of restaurants are tradition for many Korean families who simply don't want to cook that day. The army stew is very cheap and tastes great. You won't get a value item like this in many American places so just give it a try. The food comes out fast but don't go into Korean restaurants expecting the best service. The best service is relative because there are different styles of what is good. In Korea, the style of good service is to not bother the table unless they call for you. I personally don't like cheese in my army stew because it makes the soup too creamy, but if you like creaminess cheese is the way to go. Other than this, I can see myself coming back.< /Review>< userid>
109248116938089034051< /userid>

< username>
John Mitchell<//username>
< Text>
Happy overall.
No troubles with the shipping, everything arrived in good order.
Really happy with the GAN 251M.

But I'm not terribly happy with the "Rubik's Connected replacement stickers", for 3 main reasons.
This is not intended to be a rant, just want to capture the points as clearly as I can :)
1 - I don't like the clear applicator tape - it's frosted, which made it very reflective, and difficult to see the placement. Also I seemed to have the opposite problem from what was mentioned in the helpful sticker-application video: my stickers would not leave the backing and adhere to the clear tape - even rolling it back didn't work; I had to almost ply each sticker off the backing and make sure it didn't shift on the clear tape.
2 - I find the sticker placement extremely biased towards the center, where there is around 1/2mm to all the touching-edges, and more like 2-3mm to the outside edges. Made placement extremely challenging and could afford a little more spread in the placement.
3 - I went with the "Bright" color scheme to try to match my GAN 11 M pro and GAN 251M - and comparing the stickers to those stickerless, it's pretty close....except for the GREEN - the "lime tree green" is much more dull and sickly looking compared to what I saw in the Sticker Picker and on my GANs (which I believe are the "bright" scheme?). (eg. Blue is really close, as are red/yellow/orange - green is different, and difficult to capture in the attached photos.< /Text>

Then after a bit I got this pretty nice email from speedcubeshop ‚ÄúA large number of packages have been experiencing delays due to inclement weather conditions. These delays are impacting all mail carriers but we remain in close contact with each carrier and are told that the situation appears to be gradually improving.
Providing you with the best experience is our priority and we hope that these weather delays do not reflect negatively on our service. We are doing everything we can to stay updated and are always just an email or phone call away should you have any questions or concerns.‚Äù It was nice if them to reach out and let me know why there were delays instead of keeping me in the dark. The shipping times are the only reason I am giving this 4 stars is because of the shipping times I mentioned. While I am totally cool with spend more get more but it seemed like it was still just too late to just be from covid and weather when there was already a 5-day window to get it delivered.

Ok, where do I start? The beginning?
My son asked for some things from SCS for Christmas and I threw in a few extra items... he was STOKED {cubing lube? it's a thing...a cube tree ornament? still in his room!} Ok, so I bought him some items, they arrived quickly and as expected... What WASN'T expected was a personal email from the shop owner to thank you for my order {let's just say I shop a lot, and I mean a LOT online, to get a PERSONAL thank you is, well, pretty much unheard of!!}... my son was unusually excited about this- so I asked Cameron if he would kindly email my son... which he promptly did~ resulting in some serious stoke in my 13 year old {as a Mom, it was pretty cute!
